{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_29","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"test_generation_failed|generated_loc|test_file|metadata_file|placeholder|This is just a placeholder|Human intervention|failure\\\" -S human-intervention-logs build stats forge . | sed -n '1,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Confirm the edit addresses the actual JVM runtime failure, such as changed runtime behavior, missing test resources, service loading changes, dependency conflicts, classpath/module issues, initialization order, changed exception types, or changed API semantics that only fail during execution.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:78:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:85:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the Java runtime failure it fixes.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:97:- CI failures indicate the Java runtime problem is not actually fixed.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:113:- For swallowed exceptions: say that catching or ignoring the failing exception hides the runtime failure instead of proving the library behavior works.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:115:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:125:- Bad runtime repair that swallows the failure:\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:49:   - Confirm the edit addresses the actual Java compilation failure, such as renamed classes, changed method signatures, module boundaries, annotation processors, or dependency coordinates.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:75:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:82:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library and the compile failure it fixes.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:94:- CI failures indicate the compile problem is not actually fixed.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:111:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:98:- For unverified `catch (Error)`: say that dynamic class loading tests should verify Native Image failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` and re-throw any other error.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:112:- Scaffold-only placeholder:\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:118:        System.out.println(\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\");\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:92:- CI failures point to a real regression or invalid update.\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:16:1. Reproduce the failure:\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:67:- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\nbuild/tests/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/63a3cec689f8a414009eab22ca734ad8.out:260:This is just a placeholder, implement your test\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring